name: You Can't Always Get What You Want SIGNED by author Sam Cutler - Grateful Dead Rolling Stones memoir
description:
"You Can't Always Get What You Want" - an exhilarating, all-access rock memoir from someone who has seen and done it all - our friend Sam Cutler, the former tour manager of the Rolling Stones and the Grateful Dead.  

We are very excited to partner with the author and offer these exclusive AUTOGRAPHED copies of his book, a 336 page trade paperback published by ECW press.  These signed copies are usually only available directly through Cutler himself, who lives in Australia - we are honored to be distributing them for him here in the states!

Filled with intimate portraits of other stars of the psychedelic circus that was the music industry in the 1960s and 1970sâincluding Janis Joplin, Jimi Hendrix, the Band, the Allman Brothers, Pink Floyd, and Eric Claptonâthis account is an ideal resource for any music fan. Includes a detailed explanation of the infamous Rolling Stones concert in Altamont, where a man in the crowd was killed by the Hells Angels.

A highly entertaining and informative memoir from start to finish, peppered with many classic rock n roll stories from a groundbreaking era - you'll find it hard to put down once you start reading!
